@baseUrl = http://localhost:7860

###
### ── Utility ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
###

### Health check
GET {{baseUrl}}/health

### All available tasks
GET {{baseUrl}}/tasks

### Action + observation JSON schema
GET {{baseUrl}}/schema

### Environment metadata
GET {{baseUrl}}/metadata

### Oracle baseline (perfect play on all tasks — takes ~5s)
GET {{baseUrl}}/baseline


###
### ── Task 1: Single-Order Warehouse Assignment ────────────────────────────
###
### Goal: pick the BEST warehouse for one order.
### Allowed actions: assign_warehouse, noop
###

### 1a. Reset Task 1 (seed 0)
POST {{baseUrl}}/reset
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "task_id": "task_1",
  "seed": 0
}

### 1b. Assign order O1 to warehouse W1 (likely the best choice — check score)
POST {{baseUrl}}/step
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "action_type": "assign_warehouse",
  "order_id": "O1",
  "warehouse_id": "W1"
}

### 1c. Check state (stock levels update after assignment)
GET {{baseUrl}}/state

### 1d. Grade the episode
POST {{baseUrl}}/grader


### 1e. Reset Task 1 seed 1 (best warehouse may differ — test variability)
POST {{baseUrl}}/reset
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "task_id": "task_1",
  "seed": 1
}

### 1f. Try the wrong warehouse — expect partial or zero score
POST {{baseUrl}}/step
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "action_type": "assign_warehouse",
  "order_id": "O1",
  "warehouse_id": "W2"
}

### 1g. Grade after wrong warehouse
POST {{baseUrl}}/grader


###
### ── Task 2: Multi-Order Fulfillment Triage ──────────────────────────────
###
### Goal: serve as many high-priority orders as possible given scarce stock.
### Demand > supply — you MUST delay or split some orders.
### Allowed actions: assign_warehouse, split_shipment, delay_order,
###                  prioritize_order, noop
###

### 2a. Reset Task 2 (seed 0)
POST {{baseUrl}}/reset
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "task_id": "task_2",
  "seed": 0
}

### 2b. Check state — inspect stock levels vs order demand
GET {{baseUrl}}/state

### 2c. Assign a high-priority (platinum/gold) order first
POST {{baseUrl}}/step
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "action_type": "assign_warehouse",
  "order_id": "O1",
  "warehouse_id": "W1"
}

### 2d. Assign another high-priority order
POST {{baseUrl}}/step
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "action_type": "assign_warehouse",
  "order_id": "O2",
  "warehouse_id": "W2"
}

### 2e. Split a medium-priority order across two warehouses
POST {{baseUrl}}/step
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "action_type": "split_shipment",
  "order_id": "O3",
  "allocations": [
    {"warehouse_id": "W1", "quantity": 1},
    {"warehouse_id": "W2", "quantity": 1}
  ]
}

### 2f. Delay a low-priority order (stock exhausted)
POST {{baseUrl}}/step
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "action_type": "delay_order",
  "order_id": "O6",
  "reason": "Insufficient stock — lower priority customer deprioritised"
}

### 2g. State after triage decisions
GET {{baseUrl}}/state

### 2h. Grade the triage episode
POST {{baseUrl}}/grader


### 2i. Reset Task 2 seed 2 — different order mix
POST {{baseUrl}}/reset
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "task_id": "task_2",
  "seed": 2
}

### 2j. Prioritize an order before assigning
POST {{baseUrl}}/step
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "action_type": "prioritize_order",
  "order_id": "O1",
  "reason": "Platinum customer with express SLA"
}

### 2k. Assign after prioritizing
POST {{baseUrl}}/step
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "action_type": "assign_warehouse",
  "order_id": "O1",
  "warehouse_id": "W1"
}

### 2l. Grade
POST {{baseUrl}}/grader


###
### ── Task 3: Cascade Recovery ────────────────────────────────────────────
###
### Goal: recover from a supplier cancellation without collateral damage.
### Allowed actions: escalate_supplier, refund_or_compensate, reroute_order,
###                  delay_order, noop
###

### 3a. Reset Task 3 (seed 0)
POST {{baseUrl}}/reset
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "task_id": "task_3",
  "seed": 0
}

### 3b. Escalate to supplier first
POST {{baseUrl}}/step
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "action_type": "escalate_supplier",
  "order_id": "O1",
  "reason": "Supplier cancelled — requesting emergency restock"
}

### 3c. Reroute order to alternate warehouse
POST {{baseUrl}}/step
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "action_type": "reroute_order",
  "order_id": "O1",
  "warehouse_id": "W2"
}

### 3d. Compensate customer for delay
POST {{baseUrl}}/step
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "action_type": "refund_or_compensate",
  "order_id": "O1",
  "reason": "Supplier disruption — compensating with voucher"
}

### 3e. Grade task 3
POST {{baseUrl}}/grader


###
### ── Negative / Edge Case Tests ───────────────────────────────────────────
###

### N1. Invalid action type — expect -0.5 reward
POST {{baseUrl}}/step
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "action_type": "do_magic",
  "order_id": "O1"
}

### N2. assign_warehouse missing warehouse_id — expect validation error
POST {{baseUrl}}/step
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "action_type": "assign_warehouse",
  "order_id": "O1"
}

### N3. split_shipment missing allocations — expect validation error
POST {{baseUrl}}/step
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "action_type": "split_shipment",
  "order_id": "O1"
}

### N4. Action disallowed for current task (reroute_order not allowed in task_1)
### First reset to task_1, then try reroute_order
POST {{baseUrl}}/reset
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "task_id": "task_1",
  "seed": 0
}

### N4b. Now send a disallowed action — expect negative reward
POST {{baseUrl}}/step
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "action_type": "reroute_order",
  "order_id": "O1",
  "warehouse_id": "W2"
}

### N5. Repeat the same action twice — expect is_repeat penalty in second step
POST {{baseUrl}}/reset
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "task_id": "task_2",
  "seed": 0
}

### N5a. First delay (valid)
POST {{baseUrl}}/step
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "action_type": "delay_order",
  "order_id": "O6",
  "reason": "Low priority"
}

### N5b. Repeat exact same delay — expect lower reward (is_repeat = true)
POST {{baseUrl}}/step
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "action_type": "delay_order",
  "order_id": "O6",
  "reason": "Low priority"
}

### N6. Step after episode is done — should return done=true, reward=0
### (Run after any graded complete episode)
POST {{baseUrl}}/step
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "action_type": "noop"
}
